</table>
<p>The <b>history of film</b> spans over a hundred years, from the latter part of the <a href="/wiki/19th_century" title="19th century">19th century</a> to the beginning of the <a href="/wiki/21st" title="21st" class="mw-redirect">21st century</a>. Motion pictures developed gradually from a carnival novelty to one of the most important tools of <a href="/wiki/Communication" title="Communication">communication</a> and <a href="/wiki/Entertainment" title="Entertainment">entertainment</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Mass_media" title="Mass media">mass media</a> in the <a href="/wiki/20th_century" title="20th century">20th century</a>. <a href="/wiki/Film" title="Film">Motion picture films</a> have had a substantial impact on <a href="/wiki/The_arts" title="The arts">the arts</a>, <a href="/wiki/Technology" title="Technology">technology</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Politics" title="Politics">politics</a>.</p>
